
## üìå Overview  
This repository is a **comprehensive collection of Machine Learning (ML) concepts and algorithms**, covering the fundamentals up to **K-Means Clustering**. The goal is to provide a structured learning path for beginners and practitioners looking to strengthen their ML foundation.  

## üìÇ Repository Contents  
The repository includes Jupyter Notebooks explaining **each ML concept with theoretical insights and Python implementations** using real-world datasets.  

### **1Ô∏è‚É£ Introduction to Machine Learning**  
- What is Machine Learning?  
- Types of ML: **Supervised vs. Unsupervised Learning**  
- Overview of the ML Pipeline (Data Preprocessing ‚Üí Model Building ‚Üí Evaluation)  
- Key Libraries: **Scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn**  

### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Data Preprocessing & Feature Engineering**  
- Handling **Missing Data** (Imputation techniques)  
- **Feature Scaling** (Normalization vs. Standardization)  
- **Encoding Categorical Variables** (One-Hot, Label Encoding)  
- **Feature Selection** & Dimensionality Reduction  

### **3Ô∏è‚É£ Supervised Learning Algorithms**  
#### **üîπ Regression Models**  
- **Linear Regression** (Simple & Multiple Regression)  
- **Polynomial Regression**  
- **Ridge & Lasso Regression** (Regularization techniques)  
- Model Performance Metrics: **MAE, MSE, RMSE, R¬≤ Score**  

#### **üîπ Classification Models**  
- **Logistic Regression** (Binary & Multi-Class Classification)  
- **Decision Trees** (Entropy, Gini Index)  
- **Random Forest Classifier** (Ensemble Learning)  
- **Support Vector Machine (SVM)** (Linear & Kernel-based)  
- Model Evaluation Metrics: **Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score, AUC-ROC**  

### **4Ô∏è‚É£ Unsupervised Learning Algorithms**  
#### **üîπ Clustering Techniques**  
- **K-Means Clustering** (Elbow Method, Silhouette Score)  
- Introduction to **Hierarchical Clustering** (Agglomerative & Divisive)  

## üõ†Ô∏è Technologies Used  
